DANIEL DUNNIGAN, Appellant, v. THOMAS HENDERSON, et al., Respondents.

Before Speir and Freedman, JJ.

Decided June 6, 1881. Appeal from judgment entered upon the verdict of a jury, and from an order denying a motion for a new trial upon the minutes. Thomas <6 Wilder, attorneys, and E. P. Wilder, of counsel, for appellant. James K. Hill, Wing & Bhoudy, attorneys, and .Joseph A. Bhoudy, of counsel, for respondents.

No opinion.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
